{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BPcJXLFHUGxxFpsPYBDhDA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `crdb-certs` secret is mounted at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs`. So I need to update `crdb-certs` for SQL to work.\n\nNow let me generate the new node cert. I'll use the openssl-toolbox to do this:\n\n1. Generate a new node key (keep or replace)\n2. Generate a CSR using the existing node.cnf\n3. Sign with CA for 365 days\n4. Extract the new cert and key\n5. Update secrets\n\nFor signing, I need to handle the extensions properly. The node.cnf has `req_extensions = v3_req`, but when signing with `openssl x509 -req`, I need to use `-extfile` and `-extensions` to transfer the extensions.\nI can reference the `v3_req` section directly in the signing command by pointing to the node.cnf file, which should preserve all the necessary extensions. Then I'll execute this in the toolbox pod.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":578,"cache_read_input_tokens":32122,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":578},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40b5eac9-9f12-43ef-942e-bf88778c576c","uuid":"b36f5b81-53c1-4899-a13b-3012906bf4fc","request_id":"req_011CcensVD88T6RAvzzKLnAd"}
