{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YNWxf3UEKN4zEPDBAbf9j2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is running but can't contact the other nodes. This might be because the other nodes still have the old certs and the cert mismatch is causing a TLS handshake failure. The pod's readiness probe might be checking SQL connectivity.\n\nActually wait - the pods `crdb-cluster-1` and `crdb-cluster-2` are still running with the old certs from `crdb-certs` (which is now updated). Since it's a secret volume, Kubernetes updates the secret content in the pod's volume after a short delay (usually within a minute or so). But this might not be happening yet since the nodes haven't been restarted.\nSo the real problem is that `crdb-cluster-0` got restarted and picked up the new cert, but the other two nodes are still running with their old certs in memory. Even if the secret on disk has been updated, CockroachDB won't use the new cert until it reloads or restarts. Since the other nodes are still running with their old certificates, they should be able to verify crdb-cluster-0's new cert since it's signed by the same CA. The TLS handshake shouldn't fail, so this might just be a timing issue with the readiness probe during startup. I should wait a bit longer and check the pod status again.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":549,"cache_read_input_tokens":37750,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":549},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40b5eac9-9f12-43ef-942e-bf88778c576c","uuid":"539c4aa9-69b3-43c2-9560-4abc6a6350de","request_id":"req_011Cceo9DJrFyryPMsTJNYg5"}
