{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MxYgn7tYJWmHziB3KFGsLi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"State `0A` = LISTEN, `06` = TIME_WAIT.\n\nPort `6691` in hex is `26257` in decimal. Port `1F90` in hex is `8080` in decimal.\n\nSo node 0 is:\n- LISTEN on port 26257 (`6691`)\n- LISTEN on port 8080 (`1F90`)\n- TIME_WAIT connections to nodes 1 and 2 on port 26257\n\nThe connections from node 0 to nodes 1 (`1300F40A` in little-endian = 10.244.0.19) and 2 (`1400F40A` = 10.244.0.20) are in TIME_WAIT state. \n\nLooking at the IPv6 entries, node 0 is also listening on both ports across all interfaces, and there are TIME_WAIT connections on port 26257 to other nodes. The TCP connections appear to have closed gracefully, but the TLS handshakes are timing out from node 1's perspective.\n\nThe test output shows node 1 (10.244.0.19) successfully established a TCP connection to node 0 (10.244.0.21) on port 26257, but the TLS handshake itself timed out during the read phase. This is puzzling because the TCP connection succeeded, so the issue must be happening at the TLS layer—either the certificate presentation or validation is hanging.\n\nI'm wondering if the problem is that nodes 1 and 2 had their secret volumes updated with new certificates, but they're still running with the old certs loaded in memory. Though CockroachDB does reload certs from disk during TLS handshakes in some versions, so that might not be it. Or maybe there's a Kubernetes network policy restricting traffic, or the StatefulSet has some network configuration I'm missing.\n\nActually, the simpler explanation could be that when `crdb-cluster-0` was deleted and recreated, the headless service DNS didn't propagate correctly, making node 0 unreachable. But that doesn't quite fit either—node 1's connection reached the TCP level with an i/o timeout rather than a connection refused error, which means DNS resolved and TCP connected. So the issue is specifically with the TLS handshake timing out.\n\nLet me check the CockroachDB logs on nodes 1 and 2 to see if they're reporting any TLS certificate errors related to node 0.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":819,"cache_read_input_tokens":45317,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":819},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40b5eac9-9f12-43ef-942e-bf88778c576c","uuid":"ea155925-62b1-42e6-a6f3-d77723f40a6a","request_id":"req_011CceoRrk4anEkkpPfQTssY"}
